records.addlTxt:
Defendant Chad C Catlin in court with attorney Sarvan Singh.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed by operation of law. Court conducts plea colloquy with defendant.  State makes sentencing recommendation.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 YEARS IMPRISONMENT
  - 2 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  - 2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S)

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling;

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.

*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.


FINE: $1,469.00 (apply cash bail and refund balance to poster)

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (apply cash bail and refund balance to poster)
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

CONDITION TIME: 270 days Huber with release for work and/or treatment.  

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.  

Defense has 7 days to file sentence credit calculation. 

Court will allow transfer to Dane County with NO electronic monitoring.
